<br>
1)  McDonald's brewed their coffee about 16-20 degrees hotter than the industry standard. <br>
<br>
2)  The two reasons for doing this were: a) they thought it tasted better; and b) there were fewer refills for patrons who drank their coffee in the store (hotter coffee to longer to drink)<br>
<br>
3)  McDonalds knew that the increased temperature of the coffee was causing more serious burns on those occassions when it was spilled<br>
<br>
4)  Depspite this they decided the lower cost/inreased profit margin was good enough to continue brewing it at higher temperatures<br>
<br>
5)  Most of the verdict was based on punitive damages, which are only awardable based upon conduct which amounts to something more than simple negligence, typically willful, wanton, reckless or intentional conduct. <br>
<br>
6)  While I don't recall the original verdict, it was in the neighborhood of 2.5 million.<br>
<br>
7)  The case occurred in a jurisdiction where culpability on the plaintiff is not a complete defense.  The jury apportions negligence to each party and then the final verdict is reduced by the same percentage of negligence as was attributed to the plaintiff<br>
<br>
8)  The trial judge reduced the jury's verdict on the grounds that he found it excessive to something around $300k<br>
<br>
9)  The judge further reduced her verdict by the percentage that jury attributed to the plaintiff for that event.  <br>
<br>
The jury system will always create results that you don't agree with, but so will any other system in place.  In general I think it does a pretty good job, although I see results all the time I think are wrong.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1594<br> <font color=#333399>(2/13/02 9:44:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: BSI suing Mythic RE:IRL Auctions - Enjoy Scirocco</span><hr size=1> Saurin CoTG says:  <b><i>The jury system will always create results that you don't agree with, but so will any other system in place.</b></i><br>
